card.name: Blue-Eyes White Dragon
card.description: This legendary dragon is a powerful engine of destruction. Virtually invincible, very few have faced this awesome creature and lived to tell the tale.

card.name: Summoned Skull
card.description:
A fiend with dark powers for confusing the enemy. Among the Fiend-Type monsters, this monster boasts considerable force.

(This card is always treated as an "Archfiend" card.)

card.name: Dark Magician
card.description: ''The ultimate wizard in terms of attack and defense.''

card.name: Red-Eyes Black Dragon
card.description: ''A ferocious dragon with a deadly attack.''

card.name: Gaia The Fierce Knight
card.description: A knight whose horse travels faster than the wind. His battle-charge is a force to be reckoned with.

card.name: Giant Soldier of Stone
card.description: A giant warrior made of stone. A punch from this creature has earth-shaking results.

card.name: Millennium Shield
card.description: A famous shield said to belong to an ancient Egyptian Pharaoh. Legends tell of its power to block any strong attack.

card.name: Oppressed People
card.description: They are oppressed, but believe they will have their freedom someday.

card.name: D.D. Trainer
card.description: A poor goblin that was sucked into a different dimension. However, he's doing his best with his new destiny.

card.name: Gogiga Gagagigo
card.description: His soul long-since collapsed, his body recklessly continues onward, driven by a lust for more power. He no longer resembles his former self....

card.name: Neo Aqua Madoor
card.description: The true nature of this wizard, who rules all water. It defends itself with a vast, impenetrable wall of ice.

card.name: Curse of Dragon
card.description: A wicked dragon that taps into dark forces to execute a powerful attack.

card.name: Aqua Madoor
card.description: A wizard of the waters that conjures a liquid wall to crush any enemies that oppose him.

card.name: Prevent Rat
card.description: This creature is shielded with a tough hide of hair and is excellent at defending itself.

card.name: Ushi Oni
card.description: A bull fiend restored by the dark arts, this monster appears out of a jar.

card.name: Island Turtle
card.description: A huge turtle that is often mistaken for an island.

card.name: Earthbound Spirit
card.description: A vengeful creature formed by the spirits of fallen warriors, it drags any who dare approach it into the deepest bowels of the earth.

card.name: Inpachi
card.description: A log that attacks lost travelers in the forest. Originally a big tree, it was cut down and possessed by a wicked spirit.

card.name: People Running About
card.description: Although they always suffer in silence, they swear an oath to inevitably revolt.

card.name: United Resistance
card.description: The people that gather to swear to fight their oppressors. A revolution is coming.

card.name: Acrobat Monkey
card.description: An autonomous monkey type robot which was developed with cutting-edge technology. It moves very acrobatically.

card.name: Skull Dog Marron
card.description: A lost dog that wandered off 1000 years ago. He's still waiting for his master to come for him.

card.name: Shadow Specter
card.description: Powerful in groups, this animal spirit can be found in the wastelands.

card.name: Beaver Warrior
card.description: What this creature lacks in size it makes up for in defense when battling in the prairie.

card.name: Saggi the Dark Clown
card.description: This clown appears from nowhere and executes very strange moves to avoid enemy attacks.

card.name: Griffore
card.description: This monster's tough hide deflects almost any attack.

card.name: Torike
card.description: ''Although a poor defender, this monster's sharp horn gives it an edge when attacking.''

card.name: Big Insect
card.description: A giant ant that dwells in the jungle, it is powerful whether attacking or defending.

card.name: Giant Flea
card.description: A massive flea that feeds on the blood of its enemies.

card.name: Mammoth Graveyard
card.description: A mammoth that protects the graves of its pack and is absolutely merciless when facing grave-robbers.

card.name: Wolf
card.description: Dis alpha wolf yoozes his sense a smell ta find da enemy. 'ey, quit sniffin at my socks!

card.name: Kojikocy
card.description: A man-hunter with powerful arms that can crush boulders.

card.name: Jellyfish
card.description: An almost invisible, semi-transparent jellyfish that drifts in the sea.

card.name: Uraby
card.description: Fast on its feet, this dinosaur rips enemies to shreds with its sharp claws.

card.name: King of Yamimakai
card.description: Wields the power of darkness to destroy its enemies.

card.name: Sleeping Lion
card.description: A ferocious animal that sleeps all day. Sometimes it's better to let Sleeping Lions lie.

card.name: Dark Plant
card.description: ''This mutant flower draws its power from pollutants and the dark forces.''

card.name: The 13th Grave
card.description: A zombie that suddenly appeared from plot #13 - an empty grave.

card.name: The Judgement Hand
card.description: An all-powerful hand that delivers ruthless attacks.

card.name: Ancient Jar
card.description: ''A very fragile jar that contains something ancient and dangerous.''

card.name: Dark King of the Abyss
card.description: It's said that this King of the Netherworld once had the power to rule over the dark.

card.name: Turtle Tiger
card.description: A tiger encased in a protective shell that attacks with razor-sharp fangs.

card.name: Water Omotics
card.description: Transforms the water overflowing from a jar into attacking dragons.

card.name: Ancient Tree of Enlightenment
card.description: ''This ancient arbor uses its extensive knowledge to avoid the damage of enemy attacks.''

card.name: Tao the Chanter
card.description: ''Master of Yin and Yang, this wizard handles a delicate balance of spells and counter spells.''

card.name: Change Slime
card.description: A slime that can morph and adopt the shape and size of any monster it chooses.

card.name: Toon Alligator
card.description: An alligator monster straight from the cartoons.

card.name: Dark Rabbit
card.description: He leaps up, down, and all around! Nobody can lay a hand on this funny bunny.

card.name: Blocker
card.description: Constructed from several components, this monster can launch them in a pincer attack.

card.name: Golgoil
card.description: An iron giant that appears from a dimensional rift.

card.name: Kappa Avenger
card.description: ''An amphibian that sold his soul for unlimited power to avenge his late friend.''

card.name: Destroyer Golem
card.description: A golem with a massive right hand for crushing its victims.

card.name: Garvas
card.description: ''A wicked beast that resembles a winged lion.''

card.name: Kattapillar
card.description: ''Attacks enemies by spitting thin, sticky webs.''

card.name: Fungi of the Musk
card.description: ''Melts away anything that dares to stand before it.''

card.name: Laughing Flower
card.description: ''A flower whose laugh can confuse the minds of enemies.''

card.name: Bean Soldier
card.description: A plant-warrior that attacks with seeds and sword.

card.name: Bone Mouse
card.description: ''A mouse that has returned as a zombie to seek revenge on cats.''

card.name: Yormungarde
card.description: ''An extremely long snake that dwells in the world of myth.''

card.name: Pale Beast
card.description: With skin tinged a bluish-white, this strange creature is a fearsome sight to behold.

card.name: Ancient Lizard Warrior
card.description: Before the dawn of man, this lizard warrior ruled supreme.

card.name: Red Archery Girl
card.description: A mermaid archer that hides in a protective shell, waiting for the right moment to strike.

card.name: Grand Tiki Elder
card.description: A masked monster that wields the most deadly of curses.

card.name: Melchid the Four-Face Beast
card.description: This monster has four different masks for four different attacks.

card.name: Souls of the Forgotten
card.description: A wicked spirit created by the hateful souls of those who fell in battle. It grows by assimilating the souls of its enemies.

card.name: The Portrait's Secret
card.description: A portrait cursed by the artist, it is said to bring ill fortune to anyone who owns it.

card.name: The Gross Ghost of Fled Dreams
card.description: This monster feeds on the dreams of an unwary sleeper, dragging the victim into eternal slumber.

card.name: Headless Knight
card.description: A haunted spirit of a falsely accused knight who wanders in search of truth and justice.

card.name: The Earl of Demise
card.description: This gentlemanly creature is extremely wicked, feared by man and fiend alike.

card.name: Gigobyte
card.description: He has a tranquil soul, but carries a destiny that one day his heart shall be tainted by evil....

card.name: Fiend Scorpion
card.description: A huge scorpion inhabited by the soul of a fiend. Usually it holds back, but has untapped potential.

card.name: Goblin Calligrapher
card.description: A Goblin who devotes himself to mastering perfect calligraphy of the word "False". He gives his all to each stroke.

card.name: Swords of Revealing Light
card.description: After this card's activation, it remains on the field, but you must destroy it during the End Phase of your opponent's 3rd turn. When this card is activated: If your opponent controls a face-down monster, flip all monsters they control face-up. While this card is face-up on the field, your opponent's monsters cannot declare an attack.

card.name: Waboku
card.description: You take no battle damage from your opponent's monsters this turn. Your monsters cannot be destroyed by battle this turn.

card.name: Nightmare's Steelcage
card.description: This card remains on the field for 2 of your opponent's turns. While this card is face-up on the field, no monsters can attack.

card.name: Shield & Sword
card.description: Switch the original ATK and DEF of all face-up monsters currently on the field, until the end of this turn.

card.name: Share the Pain
card.description: Tribute 1 monster; make your opponent Tribute 1 monster (for no effect).

card.name: Backup Soldier
card.description: While there are 5 or more monsters in your Graveyard: Target up to 3 non-Effect Monsters with 1500 or less ATK in your Graveyard; add them to your hand.

card.name: Adhesion Trap Hole
card.description: When your opponent Summons a monster(s): Halve that monster(s)'s original ATK.

card.name: Self-Destruct Button
card.description: You can only activate this card while your Life Points are lower than your opponent's Life Points and the difference is 7000 points or more. Both players' Life Points become 0.

card.name: Back to Square One
card.description: Discard 1 card, then target 1 monster on the field; place that target on the top of the Deck.

card.name: Threatening Roar
card.description: Your opponent cannot declare an attack this turn.

card.name: Stop Defense
card.description: Select 1 Defense Position monster on your opponent's side of the field and change it to Attack Position.

card.name: Reverse Trap
card.description: Until the End Phase, all effects that add or subtract ATK or DEF are reversed. (Additions now subtract, and subtractions now add, instead. Multiplications and divisions, including halving/doubling, are not affected.)

card.name: Lightforce Sword
card.description: Banish 1 random card from your opponent's hand, face-down. During your opponent's 4th Standby Phase after this card's activation, return that card to their hand.

card.name: Block Attack
card.description: Target 1 face-up Attack Position monster your opponent controls; change that target to face-up Defense Position.

card.name: Graverobber
card.description: Select 1 Spell Card from your opponent's Graveyard. You can use it as your hand until the end of the turn. If you use it, you take 2000 points of damage.

card.name: Windstorm of Etaqua
card.description: Change the battle positions of all face-up monsters your opponent controls.

card.name: Cold Wave
card.description: This card can only be activated at the start of Main Phase 1. Until your next turn, you and your opponent cannot play or Set any Spell or Trap Cards.

card.name: Fiend Comedian
card.description: Toss a coin and call it. If you call it right, all your opponent's cards in the Graveyard are removed from play immediately. If you call it wrong, send a number of cards equal to the cards in your opponent's Graveyard from your Deck to your Graveyard.

card.name: Huge Revolution
card.description: This card can only be activated during your Main Phase when "People Running About", "Oppressed People", and "United Resistance" are face-up on your side of the field. Send all cards in your opponent's hand to the Graveyard and destroy all cards your opponent controls on the field.

card.name: Zero Gravity
card.description: Change the battle positions of all face-up monsters on the field.

card.name: Dark-Piercing Light
card.description: Flip all face-down monsters on your opponent's side of the field face-up.

card.name: Mesmeric Control
card.description: During your opponent's next turn after you activate this card, your opponent cannot change the battle positions of monsters, except with a card effect.

card.name: Skull Dice
card.description: Roll a six-sided die. All monsters your opponent currently controls lose ATK/DEF equal to the result x 100, until the end of this turn.

card.name: Gravedigger Ghoul
card.description: Select up to 2 Monster Card(s) from your opponent's Graveyard. Remove the selected card(s) from play.

card.name: The Inexperienced Spy
card.description: Select and see 1 card in your opponent's hand.

card.name: Reinforcements
card.description: Target 1 face-up monster on the field; it gains 500 ATK until the end of this turn.

card.name: Castle Walls
card.description: Increase the DEF of 1 face-up monster on the field by 500 points until the end of this turn.

card.name: Ancient Telescope
card.description: See the top 5 cards of your opponent's Deck. Return the cards to the Deck in the same order.

card.name: Curse of Fiend
card.description: Change the battle positions of all Attack Position monsters on the field to Defense Position and vice-versa. These positions cannot be changed during the turn this card is activated except by the effect of a Spell, Trap or Effect Monster Card. You can only activate this card during your Standby Phase.

card.name: Final Destiny
card.description: Discard 5 cards from your hand. Destroy all cards on the field.

card.name: Darkness Approaches
card.description: Discard 2 cards from your hand. Select 1 face-up monster and change it to face-down Defense Position.

card.name: Fairy's Hand Mirror
card.description: When your opponent activates a Spell Card that targets exactly 1 monster (and no other cards) on the field: Target another card that would be an appropriate target; that Spell now targets the new target.

card.name: Snake Fang
card.description: Decrease 1 selected monster's DEF by 500 points during the turn this card is activated.

card.name: Major Riot
card.description: You can activate this card when 1 or more of your monsters are returned from the field to your hand by your opponent's effect. Return all Monster Cards on the field to your respective hands. Both you and your opponent then Special Summon from your hand the same number of Monster Cards on the field in face-down Defense Position.

card.name: Solomon's Lawbook
card.description: Skip your next Standby Phase.

card.name: Seal of the Ancients
card.description: Pay 1000 Life Points. Pick up and see all face-down cards on your opponent's side of the field, then return them to their original positions. (The effects of the face-down cards are not activated.)

card.name: Chosen One
card.description: Select 1 Monster Card and 2 non-Monster Cards from your hand. Your opponent randomly selects 1 card among them. If it is a Monster Card, it is Special Summoned and send the remaining 2 cards to the Graveyard. If not, send all the cards to the Graveyard.

card.name: Mask of Weakness
card.description: Target 1 attacking monster; that target loses 700 ATK until the end of this turn.

card.name: Multiplication of Ants
card.description: Tribute 1 Insect-Type Monster on your side of the field. Special Summon 2 "Army Ant Tokens" (Insect-Type/EARTH/Level 4/ATK 500/DEF 1200) on your side of the field. The tokens cannot be used as a Tribute for a Tribute Summon.

card.name: Insect Imitation
card.description: Tribute 1 monster. Special Summon 1 Insect-Type monster from your Deck whose Level is 1 higher than the Tributed monster's.

card.name: Exchange
card.description: Both players reveal their hands and add 1 card from each other's hand to their hand.

card.name: Deal of Phantom
card.description: Select 1 face-up monster on the field. Increase the selected monster's ATK by 100 points for each monster in your Graveyard during the turn this card is activated. The number of monsters is applied when this card is activated.

card.name: A Feint Plan
card.description: A player cannot attack face-down monsters during this turn.

card.name: Spell Reproduction
card.description: Send 2 Spells from your hand to the GY, then target 1 Spell in your GY; add it to your hand.

card.name: The Secret of the Bandit
card.description: This card can only be activated during Main Phase 1. Select 1 face-up monster on the field. Each time the selected monster inflicts Battle Damage to your opponent's Life Points this turn, your opponent discards 1 random card.

card.name: Bubble Crash
card.description: This card can only be activated when any player has 6 or more cards on the field and/or in their hand. The player(s) then select and send cards to their respective Graveyards until the amount remaining on the field and in their hand is 5.

card.name: Dark Designator
card.description: Declare 1 Monster Card name. If the declared card is in your opponent's Deck, add 1 of that card to your opponent's hand.

card.name: Hieroglyph Lithograph
card.description: Pay 1000 Life Points. During the current Duel, your hand size limit becomes 7.

card.name: Curse of Aging
card.description: Discard 1 card from your hand. Decrease the ATK and DEF of all monsters on your opponent's side of the field by 500 points until the end of the turn this card is activated.

card.name: Non Aggression Area
card.description: You can only activate this card during your Standby Phase. Discard 1 card from your hand. Your opponent cannot Normal Summon, Set and/or Special Summon during his/her next turn.

card.name: Gather Your Mind
card.description: Add 1 "Gather Your Mind" card from your Deck to your hand. Your Deck is then shuffled. You can only use 1 "Gather Your Mind" per turn.

card.name: Sage's Stone
card.description: If you control a face-up "Dark Magician Girl": Special Summon 1 "Dark Magician" from your hand or Deck.

card.name: Dice Re-Roll
card.description: One time, during the rest of this turn, if either player(s) rolls a die (or dice), you can have the player(s) re-roll. (You can only gain this effect once per turn.)

card.name: Energy Drain
card.description: Target 1 face-up monster you control; it gains 200 ATK/DEF for each card your opponent currently has in their hand, until the end of this turn.

card.name: Jade Insect Whistle
card.description: Your opponent selects 1 Insect-Type Monster from their Deck. After shuffling the Deck, place the card on top of the Deck.

card.name: Micro Ray
card.description: Target 1 face-up monster on the field; that target's DEF becomes 0 until the end of this turn.

card.name: Order to Charge
card.description: Target 1 non-Token Normal Monster you control; Tribute that Normal Monster, and if you do, destroy 1 monster your opponent controls.

card.name: The Law of the Normal
card.description: You can only activate this card while there are 5 face-up Level 2 or lower Normal Monsters on your side of the field. Both players discard all cards in their hands, and destroy all cards on the field except Level 2 or lower Normal Monsters.

card.name: Thousand Energy
card.description: Increase the original ATK and DEF of all face-up Level 2 Normal Monsters (except Tokens) on your side of the field by 1000 points until the End Phase. Destroy all Level 2 Normal Monsters on your side of the field during the End Phase.

card.name: Triangle Power
card.description: Increase the original ATK and DEF of all face-up Level 1 Normal Monsters (except Tokens) on your side of the field by 2000 points until the End Phase. Destroy all Level 1 Normal Monsters on your side of the field during the End Phase.

card.name: Order to Smash
card.description: Target 1 Level 2 or lower non-Token Normal Monster you control; Tribute that Normal Monster, and if you do, destroy up to 2 Spells/Traps your opponent controls.

card.name: Fruits of Kozaky's Studies
card.description: Look at the top 3 cards of your Deck and return those cards to the top of the Deck in any order.

card.name: Mind Haxorz
card.description: Pay 500 Life Points. Look at your opponent's hand and all Set cards on their side of the field.

card.name: Pot of Generosity
card.description: Return 2 cards from your hand to your Deck. Then shuffle your Deck.

card.name: Simultaneous Loss
card.description: Each player sends the top card of their Deck to the Graveyard.

card.name: Destruction of Destiny
card.description: Send 3 cards from the top of your Deck to the Graveyard, and take 1000 damage for each Spell or Trap Card sent to the Graveyard this way.

card.name: Life Equalizer
card.description: Activate only when the difference between both players' Life Points is 8000 or more. Both players' Life Points become 3000.

card.name: Polymerization
card.description: Fusion Summon 1 Fusion Monster from your Extra Deck, using monsters from your hand or field as Fusion Material.

card.name: Fusion Sage
card.description: Add 1 "Polymerization" from your Deck to your hand.

card.name: Summoner of Illusions
card.description: FLIP: Tribute 1 other monster, and if you do, Special Summon 1 Fusion Monster from your Extra Deck, but destroy it during the End Phase of this turn.

card.name: Flame Swordsman
card.description: "Flame Manipulator" + "Masaki the Legendary Swordsman"

card.name: Monster Eye
card.description: You can pay 1000 Life Points; add 1 "Polymerization" from your Graveyard to your hand.

card.name: Punished Eagle
card.description: "Blue-Winged Crown" + "Niwatori"

card.name: Rose Spectre of Dunn
card.description: "Feral Imp" + "Snakeyashi"

card.name: Ryu-Kishin
card.description: A very elusive creature that looks like a harmless statue until it attacks.

card.name: Feral Imp
card.description: A playful little fiend that lurks in the dark, waiting to attack an unwary enemy.

card.name: Tyhone
card.description: Capable of firing cannonballs from its mouth for long-range attacks, this creature is particularly effective in mountain battles.

card.name: Karbonala Warrior
card.description: "M-Warrior #1" + "M-Warrior #2"

card.name: Hercules Beetle
card.description: A massive beetle with a tough carapace and a dangerous horn.

card.name: Silver Fang
card.description: A snow wolf that's beautiful to the eye, but absolutely vicious in battle.

card.name: Man-Eating Plant
card.description: ''A meat-eating plant that is attractive to the eye but dangerous when approached.''

card.name: Barox
card.description: "Frenzied Panda" + "Ryu-Kishin"

card.name: Mystic Horseman
card.description: Half man and half horse, this monster is known for its extreme speed.

card.name: Rabid Horseman
card.description: "Battle Ox" + "Mystic Horseman"

card.name: Wings of Wicked Flame
card.description: Crimson wings of fire make this a very lethal creature.

card.name: Charubin the Fire Knight
card.description: "Monster Egg" + "Hinotama Soul"

card.name: Flame Manipulator
card.description: This Spellcaster attacks enemies with fire-related spells such as "Sea of Flames" and "Wall of Fire".

card.name: Temple of Skulls
card.description: A mysterious temple of skulls and bones that pulls in unsuspecting enemies.

card.name: Rhaimundos of the Red Sword
card.description: Armed with the Sword of Crimson Flames, this warrior can bind a monster with fiery restraints.

card.name: Firegrass
card.description: A fire-breathing plant found growing near volcanoes.

card.name: M-Warrior #1
card.description: Specializing in combination attacks, this warrior uses magnetism to block an enemy's escape.

card.name: Darkfire Dragon
card.description: "Firegrass" + "Petit Dragon"

card.name: Armaill
card.description: A strange warrior who manipulates three deadly blades with both hands and his tail.

card.name: Fusionist
card.description: "Petit Angel" + "Mystical Sheep #2"

card.name: Petit Dragon
card.description: A very small dragon known for its vicious attacks.

card.name: Petit Angel
card.description: A quick-moving and tiny fairy that's very difficult to hit.

card.name: Hinotama Soul
card.description: An intensely hot flame creature that rams anything standing in its way.

card.name: Rare Fish
card.description: "Fusionist" + "Enchanting Mermaid"

card.name: Beautiful Headhuntress
card.description: A vicious creature that has decapitated numerous enemy monsters.

card.name: Enchanting Mermaid
card.description: A beautiful mermaid that lures voyagers to a watery grave.

card.name: Mavelus
card.description: "Tyhone" + "Wings of Wicked Flame"

card.name: Ground Attacker Bugroth
card.description: A surface battle robot that was once used for sea warfare.

card.name: Protector of the Throne
card.description: While the king is away, this queen protects his throne with a mighty defense.

card.name: Mystical Sheep #2
card.description: A monstrous sheep with a long tail for hypnotizing enemies.

card.name: Fireyarou
card.description: A malevolent creature wrapped in flames that attacks enemies with intense fire.

card.name: Dragoness the Wicked Knight
card.description: "Armaill" + "One-Eyed Shield Dragon"

card.name: One-Eyed Shield Dragon
card.description: This dragon wears a shield not only for its own protection, but also for ramming its enemies.

card.name: Sonic Maid
card.description: A maiden that uses sound to her advantage, she wields a scythe that's shaped like a musical note.

card.name: Giltia the D. Knight
card.description: "Guardian of the Labyrinth" + "Protector of the Throne"

card.name: Ocubeam
card.description: Frightening in appearance, this creature uses its large eyes and ears to keep track of any movement.

card.name: Metal Dragon
card.description: "Steel Ogre Grotto #1" + "Lesser Dragon"

card.name: Deepsea Shark
card.description: "Bottom Dweller" + "Tongyo"

card.name: Kaminari Attack
card.description: "Ocubeam" + "Mega Thunderball"

card.name: Vermillion Sparrow
card.description: "Rhaimundos of the Red Sword" + "Fireyarou"

card.name: Kuwagata α
card.description: A very vicious stag beetle that goes for the head.

card.name: Pragtical
card.description: "Trakodon" + "Flame Viper"

card.name: Flower Wolf
card.description: "Silver Fang" + "Darkworld Thorns"

card.name: Skullbird
card.description: "Takuhee" + "Temple of Skulls"

card.name: Kwagar Hercules
card.description: "Kuwagata α" + "Hercules Beetle"

card.name: Mega Thunderball
card.description: Rolls along the ground releasing bolts of electricity to attack its enemies.

card.name: Niwatori
card.description: Swallows enemies whole and uses their essence as energy.

card.name: Tongyo
card.description: This monster captures other fish with its long tongue and sucks the energy out of them.

card.name: Behegon
card.description: With an enormous maw and massive teeth, this monstrosity is one dangerous and strange serpent from the deep.

card.name: Steel Ogre Grotto #1
card.description: A steel idol worshipped in the Land of Machines.

card.name: Lesser Dragon
card.description: A minor dragon incapable of breathing fire.

card.name: Darkworld Thorns
card.description: A thorny plant found in the darklands that wraps itself around any unwary traveler.

card.name: Takuhee
card.description: This bird is known far and wide as a harbinger of doom.

card.name: Marine Beast
card.description: "Water Magician" + "Behegon"

card.name: Warrior of Tradition
card.description: "Sonic Maid" + "Beautiful Headhuntress"

card.name: Blue-Winged Crown
card.description: With hair shaped like a crown and a body encased in bluish white flames, this bird is a formidable sight.

card.name: Amphibious Bugroth
card.description: "Ground Attacker Bugroth" + "Defender of the Sea"

card.name: Flame Viper
card.description: A fire-breathing snake whose speed makes it a difficult target.

card.name: Sangan
card.description: If this card is sent from the field to the GY: Add 1 monster with 1500 or less ATK from your Deck to your hand, but you cannot activate cards, or the effects of cards, with that name for the rest of this turn. You can only use this effect of "Sangan" once per turn.

card.name: Kaibaman
card.description: You can Tribute this card; Special Summon 1 "Blue-Eyes White Dragon" from your hand.

card.name: Dark Eradicator Warlock
card.description: Cannot be Normal Summoned/Set. Must be Special Summoned (from your hand) by Tributing 1 "Dark Magician", and cannot be Special Summoned by other ways. Each time a Normal Spell Card is activated, inflict 1000 damage to your opponent immediately after it resolves.

card.name: Time Wizard
card.description: Once per turn: You can toss a coin and call it. If you call it right, destroy all monsters your opponent controls. If you call it wrong, destroy as many monsters you control as possible, and if you do, take damage equal to half the total ATK those destroyed monsters had while face-up on the field.

card.name: Kuriboh
card.description: During damage calculation, if your opponent's monster attacks (Quick Effect): You can discard this card; you take no battle damage from that battle.

card.name: D.D. Warrior

card.name: Javelin Beetle
card.description: This card can only be Ritual Summoned with the Ritual Spell Card, "Javelin Beetle Pact".

card.name: Fortress Whale

card.name: Dokurorider
card.description: This monster can only be Ritual Summoned with the Ritual Spell Card, "Revival of Dokurorider". You must also offer monsters whose total Level Stars equal 6 or more as a Tribute from the field or your hand.

card.name: Chimeratech Overdragon
card.description:
"Cyber Dragon" + 1+ Machine monsters
Must be Fusion Summoned. If this card is Fusion Summoned: Send all other cards you control to the GY. The original ATK/DEF of this card each become equal to the number of Fusion Materials used for its Fusion Summon x 800. Each turn, this card can attack your opponent's monsters a number of times equal to the number of Fusion Materials used for its Fusion Summon.

card.name: Destiny HERO - Dasher
card.description: Once per turn: You can Tribute 1 other monster; this card gains 1000 ATK until the End Phase. If this card attacks, change it to Defense Position at the end of the Battle Phase. One time only, when you draw a Monster Card during your Draw Phase while this card is in your Graveyard: You can reveal it; Special Summon it. This card must be in the Graveyard to activate and to resolve this effect.

card.name: Overload Fusion
card.description: Fusion Summon 1 DARK Machine Fusion Monster from your Extra Deck, by banishing Fusion Materials listed on it from your field or GY.

card.name: Elemental HERO Shining Phoenix Enforcer
card.description:
"Elemental HERO Phoenix Enforcer" + "Elemental HERO Sparkman"
Must be Fusion Summoned and cannot be Special Summoned by other ways. This card gains 300 ATK for each "Elemental HERO" card in your Graveyard. This card cannot be destroyed by battle.

card.name: Destiny HERO - Diamond Dude
card.description: Once per turn: You can excavate the top card of your Deck, and if it is a Normal Spell, send it to the GY, otherwise place it on the bottom of your Deck. During the Main Phase of your next turn, you can activate the effect of that Spell in your GY (even if you no longer control this face-up card).

card.name: Clock Tower Prison
card.description: Once per turn, during your opponent's Standby Phase: Place 1 Clock Counter on this card. While there are 4 or more Clock Counters on this card, you do not take any battle damage. If this card with 4 or more Clock Counters is destroyed and sent to the GY: Special Summon 1 "Destiny HERO - Dreadmaster" from your hand or Deck.

card.name: Destiny HERO - Double Dude
card.description: Cannot be Special Summoned. This card can attack twice during each Battle Phase. During your Standby Phase, if this card was destroyed since your last Standby Phase: You can Special Summon 2 "Double Dude Tokens" (Warrior-Type/DARK/Level 4/ATK 1000/DEF 1000). This card must be in your Graveyard to activate and to resolve this effect.

card.name: Mausoleum of the Emperor
card.description: During any Main Phase: The turn player can pay 1000 LP x the number of monsters normally needed for the Tribute Summon of a monster (max. 2000); that player Normal Summons/Sets that monster without Tributing. (This is their one Normal Summon/Set for that turn. This is not a Tribute Summon.)

card.name: Phantom Beast Cross-Wing
card.description: While this card is in the Graveyard, "Gazelle the King of Mythical Beasts" and all "Phantom Beast" monsters on the field gain 300 ATK.

card.name: Phantom Beast Wild-Horn
card.description: During battle between this attacking card and a Defense Position monster whose DEF is lower than the ATK of this card, inflict the difference as Battle Damage to your opponent.

card.name: Phantom Beast Thunder-Pegasus
card.description: When your opponent's monster declares an attack, you can remove from play this card from your Graveyard to make the Battle Damage taken by 1 "Gazelle the King of Mythical Beasts" or "Phantom Beast" monster 0. When this happens, that monster is not destroyed by battle.

card.name: Elemental HERO Phoenix Enforcer
card.description:
"Elemental HERO Avian" + "Elemental HERO Burstinatrix"
Must be Fusion Summoned and cannot be Special Summoned by other ways. This card cannot be destroyed by battle.

card.description: If this card is Special Summoned by "Clock Tower Prison": Destroy all monsters you control, except "Destiny HERO" monsters, also, after that, you can Special Summon up to 2 "Destiny HERO" monsters from your GY. After this card is Special Summoned, for the rest of this turn, "Destiny HERO" monsters you control cannot be destroyed, also you take no battle damage when they battle. The ATK/DEF of this card are equal to the combined original ATK of all other "Destiny HERO" monsters you control.

card.name: Destiny Signal
card.description: When a monster you control is destroyed by battle and sent to the GY: Special Summon 1 Level 4 or lower "Destiny HERO" monster from your hand or Deck.

card.name: Destiny HERO - Fear Monger

card.name: Destiny HERO - Dogma
card.description: Cannot be Normal Summoned/Set. Must be Special Summoned (from your hand) by Tributing 3 monsters, including at least 1 "Destiny HERO" monster. Once per turn, if you still control this face-up card during your opponent's next Standby Phase after you Special Summoned it this way: Halve your opponent's LP.

card.name: Elemental HERO Aqua Neos

"Elemental HERO Neos" + "Neo-Spacian Aqua Dolphin"
Must first be Special Summoned (from your Extra Deck) by shuffling the above cards you control into the Deck. (You do not use "Polymerization".) Once per turn: You can discard 1 card; destroy 1 random card in your opponent's hand. During the End Phase: Shuffle this card into the Extra Deck.

card.name: Elemental HERO Flare Neos
card.description:
"Elemental HERO Neos" + "Neo-Spacian Flare Scarab"
Must first be Special Summoned (from your Extra Deck) by shuffling the above cards you control into the Deck. (You do not use "Polymerization".) This card gains 400 ATK for each Spell/Trap Card on the field. During the End Phase: Shuffle this card into the Extra Deck.

card.name: Neo-Spacian Aqua Dolphin
card.description: Once per turn: You can discard 1 card; look at your opponent's hand and choose 1 monster. If you control a monster with ATK greater than or equal to the ATK of the chosen card, destroy the chosen card, and if you do, inflict 500 damage to your opponent. Otherwise, take 500 damage.

card.name: Neo Space
card.description: "Elemental HERO Neos" and all Fusion Monsters that specifically list "Elemental HERO Neos" as a Fusion Material gain 500 ATK. Fusion Monsters that specifically list "Elemental HERO Neos" as a Fusion Material do not have to activate their effects during the End Phase that shuffle them into the Extra Deck.

card.name: Sabersaurus
card.description: This normally gentle dinosaur enjoys relaxing in its nest in the prairies. If it becomes angered, it turns terribly ferocious.

card.name: Alien Mother
card.description: If this card destroys a monster with an A-Counter by battle and sends it to the Graveyard, Special Summon the destroyed monster to your side of the field at the end of the Battle Phase. When this card is removed from the field, all monsters that were Special Summoned by this card's effect are destroyed.

card.name: Cosmic Horror Gangi'el

(If a monster with an A-Counter battles an "Alien" monster, it loses 300 ATK and DEF for each A-Counter during damage calculation only.)

card.name: The Wicked Dreadroot
card.description: This card cannot be Special Summoned. This card cannot be Normal Summoned or Set except by Tributing 3 monsters. Halve the ATK and DEF of all monsters on the field, except this card.

card.name: Van'Dalgyon the Dark Dragon Lord
card.description:
If you negate the activation of an opponent's Spell/Trap Card(s), or opponent's monster effect(s), with a Counter Trap Card (except during the Damage Step): You can Special Summon this card from your hand. If Summoned this way, activate these effects and resolve in sequence, depending on the type of card(s) negated by that Counter Trap:
● Spell: Inflict 1500 damage to your opponent.
● Trap: Target 1 card your opponent controls; destroy that target.
● Monster: Target 1 monster in your Graveyard; Special Summon it.

card.name: The Selection
card.description: Pay 1000 Life Points. Negate the Summon of a monster that has the same Type as a monster on the field, and destroy it.

card.name: Arcana Knight Joker
card.description:
"Queen's Knight" + "Jack's Knight" + "King's Knight"
A Fusion Summon of this card can only be done with the above materials. Once per turn, when a Spell/Trap Card, or monster effect, is activated that targets this face-up card on the field (Quick Effect): You can discard the same type of card (Monster, Spell, or Trap); negate the effect.

card.name: Dreadscythe Harvester
card.description: You can Tribute 1 Insect-Type monster to have this card gain 500 ATK until the end of the turn.

card.name: Elemental HERO Mudballman
card.description:
"Elemental HERO Bubbleman" + "Elemental HERO Clayman"
Must be Fusion Summoned and cannot be Special Summoned by other ways.

card.name: King of Destruction - Xexex
card.description: This card cannot be Special Summoned. This card must be Tribute Summoned by Tributing 3 Fiend-Type monsters on your side of the field. If this card attacks your opponent's Life Points directly and makes them 0, the controller of this card wins the Match.

card.name: Queen of Fate - Eternia
card.description: This card cannot be Special Summoned. This card must be Tribute Summoned by Tributing 3 Fairy-Type monsters on your side of the field. If this card attacks your opponent's Life Points directly and makes them 0, the controller of this card wins the Match.

card.name: Lancer Dragonute
card.description: If this card attacks a Defense Position monster, inflict piercing battle damage to your opponent.

card.name: Mist Body
card.description: The equipped monster cannot be destroyed by battle.

card.name: White-Horned Dragon
card.description: When this card is Normal or Special Summoned: Target up to 5 Spell Cards in your opponent's Graveyard; banish those target(s), and if you do, this card gains 300 ATK for each card banished by this effect.

card.name: Uria, Lord of Searing Flames
card.description: Cannot be Normal Summoned/Set. Must be Special Summoned (from your hand) by sending 3 face-up Trap Cards you control to the Graveyard, and cannot be Special Summoned by other ways. This card gains 1000 ATK for each Continuous Trap Card in your Graveyard. Once per turn: You can target 1 Set Spell/Trap Card your opponent controls; destroy that target. Neither player can activate Spell/Trap Cards in response to this effect's activation.

card.name: Hamon, Lord of Striking Thunder
card.description: Cannot be Normal Summoned/Set. Must be Special Summoned (from your hand) by sending 3 face-up Continuous Spell Cards you control to the Graveyard, and cannot be Special Summoned by other ways. If this card destroys an opponent's monster by battle and sends it to the Graveyard: Inflict 1000 damage to your opponent. While this card is in face-up Defense Position, monsters your opponent controls cannot target monsters for attacks, except this one.

card.name: Raviel, Lord of Phantasms
card.description: Cannot be Normal Summoned/Set. Must be Special Summoned (from your hand) by Tributing 3 Fiend-Type monsters, and cannot be Special Summoned by other ways. If your opponent Normal Summons a monster(s): Special Summon 1 "Phantasm Token" (Fiend-Type/DARK/Level 1/ATK 1000/DEF 1000) for each monster Summoned, but it cannot declare an attack. Once per turn: You can Tribute 1 monster; this card gains ATK equal to the original ATK of the Tributed monster until the end of this turn.

card.name: Phantasmal Martyrs
card.description: Activate only while you have 2 or more cards in your hand, and control a face-up "Uria, Lord of Searing Flames" or "Hamon, Lord of Striking Thunder". Send your entire hand to the Graveyard to Special Summon 3 "Phantasmal Martyr Tokens" (Fiend-Type/DARK/Level 1/ATK 0/DEF 0) in Attack Position.

card.name: Elemental HERO Electrum
card.description:
"Elemental HERO Avian" + "Elemental HERO Burstinatrix" + "Elemental HERO Clayman" + "Elemental HERO Bubbleman"
Must be Fusion Summoned and cannot be Special Summoned by other ways. While face-up on the field, this card is also WIND, WATER, FIRE, and EARTH-Attribute. When this card is Fusion Summoned: Shuffle all banished cards into the Deck(s). This card gains 300 ATK for each monster your opponent controls that shares an Attribute with this card.

card.name: Helios Trice Megistus
card.description: You can Special Summon this card by Tributing 1 "Helios Duo Megistus". This card's ATK and DEF are each equal to the number of removed from play monsters x 300. After this card attacks, it can attack once more if your opponent controls a monster. If this card is destroyed by battle and sent to the Graveyard, Special Summon it during the End Phase and it gains 500 ATK and DEF.

card.name: Elemental HERO Dark Neos
card.description:
"Elemental HERO Neos" + "Neo-Spacian Dark Panther"
Must first be Special Summoned (from your Extra Deck) by shuffling the above cards you control into the Deck. (You do not use "Polymerization".) If this card is not already targeting a monster with its effect: You can target 1 face-up Effect Monster on the field; while you control this face-up card, that target's effect on the field is negated. During the End Phase: Shuffle this card into the Extra Deck.

card.name: Neo-Spacian Dark Panther
card.description: Once per turn: You can target 1 face-up monster your opponent controls; until the End Phase, this card's name becomes that monster's original name, also replace this effect with that monster's original effects (if any).

card.name: Phantom Beast Rock-Lizard
card.description: If you're Tributing a "Phantom Beast" monster or "Gazelle the King of Mythical Beasts", this card can be Normal Summoned with 1 Tribute. When this card destroys a monster by battle, inflict 500 damage to your opponent. When this card is destroyed and sent to the Graveyard by an opponent's card effect, inflict 2000 damage to your opponent.
